The paper deals with a consensus process in a communication network, which involves analyzing the behavior of a simple update rule applied to a biased initial configuration. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) for the analysis of the update rule, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) for the study of the consensus process in a network, Information Theory (cs.IT) for the analysis of convergence time, Systems and Control (cs.SY) for the modeling of the network dynamics, and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) for the study of collective behavior.
